  "title": "Quantity Surveyor #79863",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Building & Construction</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Quantity Surveyor</strong></li><li>Working Location: Sembawang</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Monday – Friday: 8.30am to 6.00pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Up to $5000 + AWS + Performance Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare key commercial documents: procurement schedule, cashflow forecast, and margin plan.</li><li>Send enquiries for assigned packages and manage clarifications.</li><li>Analyse subcontractor/supplier tenders and prepare comparisons.</li><li>Flag risks or discrepancies in tender documents to the lead estimator.</li><li>Prepare/verify quantity take‑offs and BOQs per client specs and drawings.</li><li>Coordinate with the estimating team and align with management’s strategy.</li><li>Support change management: measure/value variations, price RFPs, and issue contractual notices on time.</li><li>Assist with monthly commercial reporting (internal and client).</li><li>Track costs and margins; propose improvement measures.</li><li>Administer the main contract/subcontracts to ensure compliance.</li><li>Prepare interim/external valuations.</li><li>Maintain accurate commercial records and drawing/register control.</li><li>Assist in concluding final accounts with clients and subcontractors per agreed standards and timelines.</li><li>Support close‑out activities and apply for retention release after defect rectification.</li><li>Perform other ad hoc duties as assigned by management and supervisors.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Civil Engineering/Construction Management or relevant fields</li><li>Proven experience in tender preparation and project management.</li><li>Strong understanding of construction documentation and ISO standards.</li><li>1–3 years’ relevant experience preferred.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79863 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
